This work presents a progressive experimental framework for Multi-Robot Task Allocation (MRTA) 
using tensor-network simulation of quantum optimization circuits.
The implemented V1–V3 pipeline establishes a baseline MRTA solver, introduces an energy-based formulation, 
and extends to scalable stochastic optimization using simulated annealing. While current implementations provide a 
foundational tensor-network encoding and approximate optimization framework, the proposed future extensions
aim to explicitly characterize MRTA structural properties influencing tensor-network contraction complexity, 
investigate dynamic MRTA updates under incremental changes, and evaluate the reliability of 
approximate tensor-network simulation in producing high-quality allocation decisions.
